quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,22,"[It will be said], ",footnotes:1:Of heedlessness, or that which had sealed your hearing, your vision and your heart from guidance.
  50,23,"And his companion, [the angel], will say, "
  50,24,"[Allāh will say], "
  51,16,"Accepting what their Lord has given them. Indeed, they were before that doers of good."
  51,17,"They used to sleep but little of the night,{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., spending a portion of the night in prayer and supplication.
  51,18,"And in the hours before dawn they would ask forgiveness,"
  52,7,"Indeed, the punishment of your Lord will occur."
  52,8,"Of it there is no preventer."
  52,9,"On the Day the heaven will sway with circular motion"
  53,1,"By the star when it descends,"
  53,2,"Your companion [i.e., Muḥammad] has not strayed, nor has he erred,"
  53,3,"Nor does he speak from [his own] inclination."